Privacy Policy for Zultron

Effective Date: 12/5/2024

Introduction
Your privacy is important to us. Zultron is a simple voice to text app designed to capture your thoughts through email or directly into Obsidian (or any other app directory that supports markdown). This Privacy Policy outlines how we handle your data.

Data Collection and Usage
Zultron does not collect, store, or share any personal data. All information you enter into the app is stored locally on your device and is not transmitted to any servers or third parties.

Third-Party Services
Zultron does not use any third-party services that collect data about you.

Children’s Privacy
Zultron is suitable for users of all ages. Since we do not collect personal data, the app complies with all relevant privacy laws concerning children’s data.

Data Security
Because Zultron does not access or store your data, the security of your data is managed entirely by you. We recommend following best practices to protect your device.

Changes to this Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected in the app and updated in this document. Please check this page periodically for updates.

Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
nick@paytonsplace.net

Summary
Your data stays with you. Zultron is committed to respecting your privacy and ensuring you have a simple and secure experience.

By using Zultron, you agree to this Privacy Policy. Thank you for trusting us to support your ability to set your mind free!
